@SharkKnives.API_HostAddress = https://localhost:7008

### 1. Obter todas as facas
GET {{SharkKnives.API_HostAddress}}/api/facas
Accept: application/json

### 2. Obter faca por ID
GET {{SharkKnives.API_HostAddress}}/api/facas/1
Accept: application/json

### 3. Login
POST {{SharkKnives.API_HostAddress}}/api/auth/login
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "email": "admin@sharkknives.com",
  "password": "admin123"
}

### 4. Registrar novo usuário
POST {{SharkKnives.API_HostAddress}}/api/auth/register
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "email": "novo@sharkknives.com",
  "password": "senha123",
  "nome": "Novo Usuário"
}

### 5. Criar nova faca (requer autenticação)
POST {{SharkKnives.API_HostAddress}}/api/facas
Content-Type: application/json
Authorization: Bearer {{auth_token}}

{
  "modelo": "Nova Faca Teste",
  "material": "Aço Teste",
  "camadas": "3 Camadas",
  "pegada": "Ergonômica",
  "cabo": "Madeira Teste",
  "dimensoes": "25cm",
  "referencia": "TEST-001",
  "ativo": true
}

### 6. Atualizar faca (requer autenticação)
PUT {{SharkKnives.API_HostAddress}}/api/facas/1
Content-Type: application/json
Authorization: Bearer {{auth_token}}

{
  "id": 1,
  "modelo": "Shark Premium Atualizada",
  "material": "Aço Inox 440C Premium",
  "camadas": "3 Camadas",
  "pegada": "Ergonômica Melhorada",
  "cabo": "Madeira de Carvalho Premium",
  "dimensoes": "25cm total",
  "referencia": "SHK-P001-UPD",
  "ativo": true
}

### 7. Deletar faca (requer autenticação)
DELETE {{SharkKnives.API_HostAddress}}/api/facas/1
Authorization: Bearer {{auth_token}}